item.title: CVE-2022-2658|2024-08-03T00:46:03.605Z -- unknown -- wp%20spell%20check
item.description: The WP Spell Check WordPress plugin before 9.13 does not escape ignored words, which could allow high privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup)
